## Africana Studies Relation

Ella Fitzgerald's legacy provides rich insight into the intersections of race, gender, and music in 20th-century America. Her contributions to jazz and popular music reflect the cultural resilience and artistic excellence of African Americans. Her influence continues to resonate in Africana Studies, serving as a beacon of artistic brilliance and perseverance.

